snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a lifelong LFC fan but my God, I do miss a fit & fighting Arsenal!
I really respect Luiz for his honesty here, and he's got nothing to lose by being so honest - I think everyone could see this is not a 'fit' Arsenal team, physically or emotionally. And I think that's going to change on both fronts with Arteta, going forward.
I honestly believe Arteta - who was a magnificent player himself - will roll out a well thought through philosophy, and do so in such a way that players will buy into it. I think he'll keep / acquire only those players with the right psychological profile too, accordingly.
Albeit step by step, I honestly think Arsenal will be a different beast next year and that should make every Arsenal fan happy at the prospect. What your fans need now, above all else, is unwavering patience, faith and trust in him because it takes time.
As for this season? A lesson in patience - just like LFC had a few years ago. Worth investing in that, I reckon..
Good luck - but not too much, of course!

snippet.textDisplay: I think it’ll help them to last 90 mins if they try and dominate possession like they use to do. If they can keep possession and cut out the lazy passes that turn over that possession they will be more consistent over 90 mins, all this closing down quickly is great and all but its not an efficient way of using energy. If they stay compact and move around the field as a unit the possession game should be a breeze so long as they make sure there’s at least 2 options for a pass. Then when the other team finally gets the ball they’ll have the energy to win it back quickly and get back into position then carry on. But great win and each player should be proud of how they performed. The fans were.
